{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0655fa247ecca2195fcfee1868433477","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n**`static_verified`** — all facts passed deterministic local checks (file exists, hash matches, size matches, selector present, snippet_hash matches). Zero rejected facts. Used when `verification_mode: \"static\"` completes with no rejections.\n\n**`partial_static`** — static verifier ran but ≥1 fact failed deterministic checks (e.g. file moved, selector text changed). Factsheet is usable only if `static_factsheet_policy: \"allow\"` on the cluster.\n\n**`llm_verified`** — static phase passed, then the no-tools LLM verifier marked every surviving fact `VERIFIED`. The factsheet is semantically trusted.\n\n**`partial_llm`** — static phase passed, but the LLM verifier marked ≥1 fact `UNVERIFIED` or `AMBIGUOUS`. Only `VERIFIED` facts are stored; the rejection count is tracked in `omitted_facts`.\n\n**When each is set** (`src/cluster.ts:131`, `src/cluster.ts:175`, `src/cluster.ts:221`):\n```ts\n// After static verification\ntrustState = verification.rejectedFacts.length === 0 ? \"static_verified\" : \"partial_static\";\n\n// After LLM verification (rejectedFacts includes both static + LLM rejections)\ntrustState = rejectedFacts.length === 0 ? \"llm_verified\" : \"partial_llm\";\n```\n\n**During `cluster_refresh`** (`src/clusterRefresh.ts:176-181`), the trust state is re-inferred from `omitted_facts` count in the stored factsheet content, not re-verified — if `status === \"llm_verified\"` and `omitted_facts > 0`, it downgrades to `partial_llm`."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":112812,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b299724c-1497-410c-96dd-2f782477c674","uuid":"e87f6ecc-6cc1-4646-94dc-d3665bc1ca71"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":15067,"duration_api_ms":15036,"num_turns":1,"result":"\n\n**`static_verified`** — all facts passed deterministic local checks (file exists, hash matches, size matches, selector present, snippet_hash matches). Zero rejected facts. Used when `verification_mode: \"static\"` completes with no rejections.\n\n**`partial_static`** — static verifier ran but ≥1 fact failed deterministic checks (e.g. file moved, selector text changed). Factsheet is usable only if `static_factsheet_policy: \"allow\"` on the cluster.\n\n**`llm_verified`** — static phase passed, then the no-tools LLM verifier marked every surviving fact `VERIFIED`. The factsheet is semantically trusted.\n\n**`partial_llm`** — static phase passed, but the LLM verifier marked ≥1 fact `UNVERIFIED` or `AMBIGUOUS`. Only `VERIFIED` facts are stored; the rejection count is tracked in `omitted_facts`.\n\n**When each is set** (`src/cluster.ts:131`, `src/cluster.ts:175`, `src/cluster.ts:221`):\n```ts\n// After static verification\ntrustState = verification.rejectedFacts.length === 0 ? \"static_verified\" : \"partial_static\";\n\n// After LLM verification (rejectedFacts includes both static + LLM rejections)\ntrustState = rejectedFacts.length === 0 ? \"llm_verified\" : \"partial_llm\";\n```\n\n**During `cluster_refresh`** (`src/clusterRefresh.ts:176-181`), the trust state is re-inferred from `omitted_facts` count in the stored factsheet content, not re-verified — if `status === \"llm_verified\"` and `omitted_facts > 0`, it downgrades to `partial_llm`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"b299724c-1497-410c-96dd-2f782477c674","total_cost_usd":0.080397,"usage":{"input_tokens":2912,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":112224,"output_tokens":389,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","it